---
import SectionLayout from "../../layouts/SectionLayout.astro";

import Title from "../Title.astro";
import Description from "../Description.astro";
import { cn } from "../../utils/cn";

// Navigation Items
const navItems = [
  { id: "overview", label: "1. Executive Overview" },
  { id: "how-it-works", label: "2. How It Works" },
  { id: "backing", label: "3. Reserve Backing & Custody" },
  { id: "contract", label: "4. Smart Contract Architecture" },
  { id: "ecosystem", label: "5. Ecosystem & Liquidity" },
  { id: "tokenomics", label: "6. Tokenomics" },
  { id: "transparency", label: "7. Transparency & Reporting" },
  { id: "roadmap", label: "8. Governance & Future Roadmap" },
  { id: "security", label: "9. Security & Risk Mitigation" },
  { id: "team", label: "10. Team" },
  { id: "legal", label: "11. Legal Notice" },
];

// Content Data
const contentData = {
  overview: {
    title: "Executive Overview",
    text: `VETRA (VTR) is an institutional stablecoin backed 1:1 by U.S. dollars and deployed on the Polygon network. For each mint, the contract guarantees that total supply does not exceed the value of reserves. Reserves are updated via Chainlink Functions and recorded on-chain with an eight-decimal USD value, a timestamp, and a security identifier.

The backing is provided by FT Asset Management KB, headquartered in Stockholm, Sweden, with an initial commitment of USD 100,000,000.00 dedicated to the currency's liquidity, credibility, and stability. As of June 2026, the protocol is over-collateralized at 333% (USD $100M reserves against 30M VTR supply), providing a significant safety buffer.

Key Metrics (June 2026):
- Total Supply: 30,000,000 VTR
- Reserves in Custody: $100,000,000 USD
- Collateralization Ratio: 333%
- Market Price: ~$0.20
- Blockchain: Polygon Mainnet (Chain ID 137)
- Smart Contract: UUPS Proxy
- Reserve Custodian: FT Asset Management KB (Sweden)
- Max Wallet: 3,000 VTR (anti-whale, whitelist exceptions)
- Transfer Tax: 0%`,
  },
  "how-it-works": {
    title: "How It Works",
    text: `Proof-of-Reserves via Chainlink Functions
VETRA integrates a reserves data source maintained by FT Asset Management KB into the smart contract through Chainlink Functions. At defined intervals, the function queries FT Asset Management KB's API and returns to the contract a snapshot containing:
• Aggregate USD value (8 decimals)
• Timestamp of the reading
• Monotonic nonce (prevents replay attacks)

Mint Invariant
Every mint operation checks:
1. Reserve Freshness — The snapshot must be within its TTL (15 minutes)
2. Supply Invariant — totalSupply + mintAmount ≤ scaledReserves
If either criterion fails, the transaction is rejected. This guarantees that no VTR can be created without verified dollar backing.

Burn Mechanism
VTR can be burned natively, reducing total supply. Burning can be triggered by:
• Token holders: Standard ERC-20 burn
• Operator Burn: Authorized roles can burn from any account per operational policy`,
  },
  backing: {
    title: "Reserve Backing & Custody",
    text: `Institutional Custodian
FT Asset Management KB is a regulated financial institution headquartered in Stockholm, Sweden. Key details:
• Institution: FT Asset Management KB (Stockholm, Sweden)
• License: Regulated financial institution
• Current Reserves: $100,000,000 USD
• Beneficiary: Pedro Fares Ramos
• Entity: Vetra Foundation Ltd (Cayman Islands)
• Verification: Public API + Certificate of Custody

Public Reserve Verification
Reserves are verifiable in real-time through:
1. On-chain: Chainlink Functions snapshots recorded every 15 minutes
2. REST API: Public API from FT Asset Management KB
3. Certificate of Custody: Official PDF issued by FT Asset Management KB

Collateralization Ratio
Current ratio: 333% (USD $100M ÷ $30M total supply). This over-collateralization provides a significant safety margin against market volatility and ensures full redeemability.`,
  },
  contract: {
    title: "Smart Contract Architecture",
    text: `UUPS Proxy
VETRA uses the Universal Upgradeable Proxy Standard (UUPS), enabling:
• Upgradeability controlled by governance: Only the DEFAULT_ADMIN_ROLE can upgrade
• State preservation: All token balances and contract state survive upgrades
• Verified implementation: Contract verified on Polygonscan with green checkmark

Contract Addresses
• Proxy (UUPS): 0xAA27bd271B01dd20CcFA079800616335416c95Fd (✅ Verified)
• Implementation V2.6: 0x3241918D37d6ba63919fe9832e7C58f4821656Cb (✅ Verified)

Role-Based Access Control (RBAC)
• DEFAULT_ADMIN_ROLE: Contract governance, upgrades, pause
• MINTER_ROLE: Mint new VTR (subject to reserve check)
• BURNER_ROLE: Burn VTR (operator burn)
• PAUSER_ROLE: Emergency pause of transfers/mints/burns

Security Parameters
• Transfer Tax: 0% — No friction on transfers
• Max Wallet: 3,000 VTR — Anti-whale (exempt for whitelisted)
• Max Volume per Block: 1,000,000 VTR — Anti-manipulation
• Cooldown: 0s (disabled for growth phase)
• Reserve TTL: 15 minutes — Freshness guarantee`,
  },
  ecosystem: {
    title: "Ecosystem & Liquidity",
    text: `SushiSwap V3 Pool
VETRA's primary liquidity pool is on SushiSwap V3 (Polygon):
• Pool: VTR / USDC | Fee Tier: 0.05% (500)
• Address: 0x8478D9B6de3A4c89B4acc904C67F9fD738dE2E4A
• Current Liquidity: ~$288,000 | Active Range: $0.20 - $0.25

VTR Pioneer NFT — Pre-Sale Program
Contract: 0x4c336E0E4Da78156242f90320463F2d8e5A86D8b (Verified on Polygonscan)
The VTR Pioneer program allows early adopters to:
1. Buy a Pioneer NFT for $0.34 USDC (15% discount off the $0.40 target price)
2. Refer friends and earn +5% VTR bonus per referral (0.05 VTR per person)
3. Redeem 1 NFT → 1 VTR when the market price reaches $0.40
This mechanism builds a waiting list without cost, creates a natural price-driven launch event, protects the price floor, and rewards early supporters with referral bonuses.

Liquidity Strategy
VETRA employs a "liquidity ladder" strategy with overlapping price ranges to ensure continuous liquidity during price discovery, escalator pools that activate as the market price rises, and no gaps between ranges — preventing liquidity holes.`,
  },
  tokenomics: {
    title: "Tokenomics",
    text: `Supply
• Maximum Supply: 30,000,000 VTR
• Circulating Supply: ~921,000 VTR
• Decimals: 18 | Standard: ERC-20

Distribution
• ADM (Treasury): ~3,658 VTR — Operations, sales
• OP2 (Reserve): ~27.7M VTR — Liquidity pools, strategic
• OP3 (Burn): ~5K VTR — Permanently locked
• Pioneer NFT Contract: 400K VTR — Redemption reserve
• Other: ~921K VTR — Circulating

Price Discovery
The current market price of ~$0.20 reflects early-stage liquidity conditions on SushiSwap V3. The target stabilization price is $0.40, at which point the Pioneer NFT redemption program activates. The protocol does not employ algorithmic price controls — stability derives from:
1. Full collateralization (333% over-collateralized)
2. Transparent reserves (on-chain PoR)
3. Organic market discovery through liquidity pools
4. Anti-whale mechanisms (max wallet, per-block volume limits)`,
  },
  transparency: {
    title: "Transparency & Reporting",
    text: `On-Chain Transparency
• Event emissions: Every mint, burn, and reserve update emits on-chain events
• Real-time monitoring: All operations trackable via Polygonscan
• Reserve dashboard: Live at https://www.vetravtr.com (Real-Time Reserves section)

Off-Chain Reporting
• Periodic reports: Performance and project evolution
• Reserve snapshot history: Published with timestamps and transaction references
• KYC/AML: Conducted institutionally by the issuer and custodian

Security Audits
• Polygonscan: ✅ Verified
• GoPlus Security: ✅ Approved
• De.Fi Scanner: ✅ No rugpull risk`,
  },
  roadmap: {
    title: "Governance & Future Roadmap",
    text: `Current Phase (June 2026) — Completed:
✅ Polygon mainnet deployment
✅ UUPS proxy with verified implementation
✅ Chainlink Functions Proof-of-Reserves
✅ SushiSwap V3 liquidity pool
✅ VTR Pioneer NFT pre-sale program
✅ RBAC governance (Admin, Minter, Burner, Pauser)
✅ Real-Time Reserves dashboard on website
✅ Over-collateralization (333%)

Next Phase (Q3 2026):
🔲 Expand to additional DEXs and CEXs
🔲 Public reserves dashboard with historical snapshot explorer
🔲 Multi-source reserve data redundancy
🔲 Automated reserve update routines
🔲 VTR Pioneer NFT public mint (website integration)

Expansion Phase (Q4 2026+):
🔲 Multi-chain deployment (Base, Arbitrum)
🔲 Institutional mint/redeem portal
🔲 Payment and compliance system integrations
🔲 VTR-backed payment cards (VETRACARD)
🔲 Euro-pegged stablecoin (VTE)`,
  },
  security: {
    title: "Security & Risk Mitigation",
    text: `Protocol Security Layers
1. Economic: 1:1 invariant enforced at every mint
2. Technical: UUPS upgradeability with RBAC governance
3. Operational: 15-minute reserve freshness TTL
4. Emergency: Pausable mechanism for critical situations
5. Monitoring: Real-time event monitoring and operational alerts

Risk Factors
• Smart contract risk: Independently audited prior to public launch
• Custodial risk: Reserves held with regulated Swedish institution
• Market risk: Price discovery through organic DEX trading
• Regulatory risk: KYC/AML conducted institutionally`,
  },
  team: {
    title: "Team",
    text: `• Pedro Fares Ramos — Founder, Chairman & CEO
• Rosemberg Alves Nascimento — Co-Founder & Head of Global Partnerships
• Christine Schöberlein — European Reserve Custodian

Official Channels:
• Website: https://www.vetravtr.com
• X/Twitter: https://x.com/vetravtr
• Email: contact@vetravtr.com
• GitHub: https://github.com/vetravtr`,
  },
  legal: {
    title: "Legal Notice",
    text: `This document is strictly informational. Its content is subject to updates without prior notice to reflect contractual, operational, technological, or regulatory changes. In the event of any discrepancy, official information published through VETRA's institutional channels prevails.

VETRA — Built for stability in the next era of finance.`,
  },
};

// Styles (unchanged)
const sectionOuterClasses = cn("flex items-start w-full relative");
const sectionInnerClasses = cn("w-full h-auto py-[88px] relative");
const mainLayoutClasses = cn(
  "grid grid-cols-1 lg:grid-cols-12 gap-[72px] w-full relative z-10 items-start",
);
const navColumnClasses = cn(
  "lg:col-span-4 flex flex-col gap-4 relative min-w-0",
  "lg:sticky lg:top-24",
);
const navItemClasses = (isActive: boolean) =>
  cn(
    "flex items-center justify-between p-4 rounded-[32px] cursor-pointer transition-all duration-300 text-sm font-medium",
    isActive
      ? "bg-[#1E0B2B] text-[#B073FF] border border-[#3D1D55]"
      : "bg-transparent text-gray-400 hover:text-white hover:bg-white/5",
  );
const contentColumnClasses = cn(
  "lg:col-span-8 flex flex-col gap-2",
  "lg:sticky lg:top-24 self-start",
);
---

<SectionLayout
  outerClassName={sectionOuterClasses}
  innerClassName={sectionInnerClasses}
  autoMargin={true}
>
  <div class={mainLayoutClasses}>
    {/* Navigation Column */}
    <div class={navColumnClasses}>
      <div
        class={cn(
          "flex lg:flex-col gap-4",
          "max-lg:overflow-x-auto max-lg:pb-4 max-lg:snap-x",
          "max-w-[280px] max-md:max-w-full w-full hide-scrollbar",
        )}
        id="whitepaper-nav"
      >
        {navItems.map((item, index) => (
          <button
            class={cn(
              "nav-item whitespace-nowrap lg:whitespace-normal text-left max-lg:snap-start shrink-0",
              "px-4 py-2 min-h-[52px] rounded-full cursor-pointer",
              index === 0
                ? "bg-[#190C26] text-light-purple"
                : "text-text-grey hover:text-white transition-colors",
            )}
            data-id={item.id}
          >
            <span class="flex items-center justify-between w-full gap-4 font-serif text-[14px] leading-[18px]">
              {item.label}
              <svg
                xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg"
                width="16"
                height="16"
                viewBox="0 0 24 24"
                fill="none"
                stroke="currentColor"
                stroke-width="2"
                stroke-linecap="round"
                stroke-linejoin="round"
                class={cn("w-4 min-w-4 h-4 transition-transform")}
              >
                <path d="M5 12h14" />
                <path d="m12 5 7 7-7 7" />
              </svg>
            </span>
          </button>
        ))}
      </div>
    </div>

    {/* Content Column */}
    <div class={contentColumnClasses} id="whitepaper-content-area">
      <Title
        text={contentData.overview.title}
        className="text-left text-[24px] leading-[32px] max-md:text-[24px] max-md:leading-[32px]"
      />
      <Description
        text={contentData.overview.text}
        className="text-left text-text-grey whitespace-pre-line"
      />
    </div>
  </div>
</SectionLayout>

<script>
  const contentData = {
    overview: {
